        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-11-10 13:17:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis will duplicate actions in the jenkins verify job.  Need to understand impact of this.  Could we achieve the equivalent with the instructions here http://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/guides/onap-developer/how-to-use-docs/include-documentation.html#all-documentation and/or improvements on these?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "e01def626b528868395e6a9eb80a019b7bcc5c90",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1201,
          "name": "Cedric Ollivier",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "cedric.ollivier@orange.com",
          "username": "ollivier"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-11-10 13:38:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm updating the patchset to pull only 1 depth what is very good here. I think the doc could skip the submodules part. Or it's better to ask for a recursive clone as Jenkins does.\n\nMy main point is we can't ensure how the user clones the repository. Then Pulling the submodules is mandatory (or checking that it's has been done). It costs nothing even if it has already be done (e.g. in Jenkins jobs).\n\nRegarding the doc, I precise it's useless to ask installing requirements as they're installed via tox in virtualenv.\n\nThe next two commands could be enough.\n$ git clone http://gerrit.onap.org/r/doc\n$ cd tox && tox",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
